HEADWORD: Blackwood
<hw>Black"wood</hw> <pr>(bl⟦acr⟧k"w⟦oocr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
name given to several dark-colored timbers. The East Indian black wood
is from the tree <spn>Dalbergia latifolia</spn>.</def>
<rj><au>Balfour.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

